Dom and Events Fundamentals
-----------------------------------

document.querySelector([select]): use to interact with the DOM in JavaScript
*.textContent : get the text of the element.

Web APIs (Application Programming Interface)

get/set input value
document.querySelector([selector]).value=[value]

[element].addEventListner: add an event to the attach element.

Always you get string from input value.

To manipulate css element in JavaScript one of the method is calling the property 
style.[any css property] the value most be string

querySelectorAll : select all occurrent of the element. That will return a NodeList

[element].classList : allow you to access the collection of classes attach to this element. And 
also have method manipulate those classes.

KeyEvent belong to global element.